cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with clustering images, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a novel method based on unmasking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The method also involves training a binary classifier, which suggests that it could fall under the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions texture classification and fine-grained object recognition, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
